## 📘 Overview

The **PetzAdop Backend** is a **Node.js & Express** REST API that powers the PetzAdop platform.  
It handles:

- Pet management (create, update, delete, list)
- Adoption and fostering applications
- User authentication and profile management
- Reviews, ratings, and comments
- Email verification and notifications
- Real-time chat between adopters and organizations

The backend is connected to a **MongoDB database** and uses **JWT for authentication**.

---

## 🚀 Key Features

### 🐶 Pet Management

- CRUD operations for pet profiles
- Upload photos/videos
- Search and filter pets by breed, age, size, and location

### 📝 Application Management

- Submit adoption/foster requests
- Approve or reject applications
- Track request status: `Pending → Accepted → Rejected`
- Schedule meet & greet appointments

### 👤 User Management

- JWT-based authentication
- User roles: adopter, shelter, foster parent
- Profile editing, password reset, and profile picture upload

### 🌟 Reviews & Ratings

- Users can leave reviews and ratings for shelters and foster organizations
- Supports comment, rating, and review type (adoption/fostering)
- Average ratings are calculated per user/organization

### 💬 Messaging System

- Real-time chat between adopters and organizations
- JWT-secured endpoints for chat messages

### 📧 Email Verification

> ⚠️ **Note:** Email verification works **only on localhost**.  
> After deploying the backend (e.g., on Render), email sending **does not work** due to SMTP/environment restrictions.  
> This feature is intended for testing in the local environment only.  
> The issue has been reported on the **GUVI platform** and is still pending resolution.

